title: Utah Food Bank
description: Utah Food Bank works with community partners and volunteers to fight hunger statewide.

title: Tali’s Fund
description: “Tali’s Fund helps fund vital research at SickKids Hospital, aimed at learning more about pediatric brain tumors.” – Tali’s Fund

title: Habitat for Humanity
description: Habitat for Humanity is a national nonprofit housing organization that builds houses through the help of volunteers for low-income families.

title: Pet Partners
description: “Pet Partner’s mission is to improve human health and well-being through the human-animal bond.” – Pet Partners

title: Second Harvest of Silicon Valley
description: Second Harvest of Silicon Valley distributes food through a network of hundreds of partners across the Santa Clara and San Mateo counties to build a hunger-free community.

title: Good + Foundation
description: Good+ Foundation is a national nonprofit that helps low-income fathers, mothers, and caregivers enroll and participate in anti-poverty programs.

title: Augie quest
description: Augie’s Quest is a charity with a mission to raise awareness and funding to find the cure for ALS.
